      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:8:4",
      "text": [
        " تُدْفَنُ الْمَرْأَةُ إِلَى وَسَطِهَا ثُمَّ يَرْمِي الْإِمَامُ وَ يَرْمِي النَّاسُ بِأَحْجَارٍ صِغَارٍ وَ لَا يُدْفَنُ الرَّجُلُ إِذَا رُجِمَ إِلَّا إِلَى حَقْوَيْهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from Muhammad Bin Isa Bin Ubeyd, from Yunus, from Sama’at, ",
          "Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> has said: ‘The woman would be buried up to her waist, then the Imam<sup>asws</sup> would pelt, and the people would pelt, with the small stones; and the man would not be buried when stoned, except up to his loins’."
        ]
      }
    },
